  <graph edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="Furnace Number Format">
      <data key="d0">Furnace Number Format</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Furnace Number Format defines the structure of a furnace identification code consisting of production line number, shift, production date, furnace number, coil number, sub-coil number, and optional appearance characteristic.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985113</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Production Line Number">
      <data key="d0">Production Line Number</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The production line number is a single digit from 1 to 4 indicating which production line produced the coil.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985113</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Shift">
      <data key="d0">Shift</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The shift is a Chinese character representing the work shift (甲, 乙, 丙) during which the production occurred.&lt;SEP&gt;Shift is a dimension with Chinese alias班次, representing work shifts including morning (早班), middle (中班), and night (晚班) shifts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dff975756a76316c5e10fbb37961c3f7</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format&lt;SEP&gt;dimensions_meta.json#shift</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985796</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Production Date">
      <data key="d0">Production Date</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The production date is an 8-digit number in YYYYMMDD format indicating the date of production.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985114</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Furnace Number Component">
      <data key="d0">Furnace Number Component</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The furnace number component indicates the sequential number of the furnace within that shift and day.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985114</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coil Number">
      <data key="d0">Coil Number</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The coil number indicates the sequential number of the coil produced from that furnace.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985114</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sub-Coil Number">
      <data key="d0">Sub-Coil Number</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The sub-coil number indicates the segment number after splitting the coil.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985114</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Appearance Characteristic">
      <data key="d0">Appearance Characteristic</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The appearance characteristic is an optional Chinese character describing the surface quality such as脆, 划, 麻点.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985114</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Example Furnace Number">
      <data key="d0">Example Furnace Number</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The example furnace number "1甲20251101-1-4-1脆" demonstrates a complete furnace number with all components.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985114</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F_FURNACE_NO">
      <data key="d0">F_FURNACE_NO</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_FURNACE_NO is a database field storing the original furnace number string entered by the user, including the characteristic Chinese character.&lt;SEP&gt;Database field representing furnace number, with synonyms: 炉号, 炉号字符串, 原始炉号.&lt;SEP&gt;F_FURNACE_NO is the original field for furnace number before formatting, with aliases: 原始炉号, 炉号字符串.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e6e25c9fd58e9924568e84459192dcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-517383c70d6bd091e78ad3ca4a0d73e0</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format&lt;SEP&gt;aliases.json#field&lt;SEP&gt;dimensions_meta.json#furnace_no</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985879</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F_FURNACE_NO_FORMATTED">
      <data key="d0">F_FURNACE_NO_FORMATTED</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_FURNACE_NO_FORMATTED is a database field storing the formatted standard furnace number without the characteristic character for associative queries.&lt;SEP&gt;F_FURNACE_NO_FORMATTED is a database field that stores the furnace number, which is unique per coil.&lt;SEP&gt;Database field representing formatted furnace number, with synonyms: 格式化炉号, 标准炉号.&lt;SEP&gt;F_FURNACE_NO_FORMATTED is the main field for furnace number after formatting, with Chinese aliases: 炉号, 标准炉号, 格式化炉号.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60d113a19c7939fa4f4a548b3cc1eba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e6e25c9fd58e9924568e84459192dcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-517383c70d6bd091e78ad3ca4a0d73e0</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#furnace_batch_no&lt;SEP&gt;aliases.json#field&lt;SEP&gt;dimensions_meta.json#furnace_no</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985879</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Furnace Number">
      <data key="d0">Furnace Number</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Furnace Number is the unique identifier for a coil, composed of a production line number, shift, production date, furnace number, coil number, sub-coil number, and an optional appearance characteristic.&lt;SEP&gt;An identifier for furnace production records; the first digit indicates the production line number, e.g., 1甲20251101-1-4-1 refers to Line 1.&lt;SEP&gt;Furnace Number is a globally unique identifier per coil, containing line/shift/date/coil information, stored in the field F_FURNACE_NO_FORMATTED. It is also known as炉号.&lt;SEP&gt;Furnace Number is a production batch identifier that often has appearance feature characters appended at the end.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a685b81b536bb4eba928bee1eb8329d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3d4d26638ad601f83b0ed6c5e5d559c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60d113a19c7939fa4f4a548b3cc1eba5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_no_format&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#line_dimension&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#furnace_batch_no&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="First Inspection Pass Rate">
      <data key="d0">First Inspection Pass Rate</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">First Inspection Pass Rate is a quality metric defined as the ratio of the sum of coil weights that pass the first inspection to the total coil weight, expressed as a percentage. It is also referred to as一次交检合格率.&lt;SEP&gt;First Inspection Pass Rate is a metric calculated from F_FIRST_INSPECTION data, measuring the percentage of items that pass the initial inspection.&lt;SEP&gt;Another metric with a different calculation method from Quality Grade Distribution, based on F_FIRST_INSPECTION.&lt;SEP&gt;First Inspection Pass Rate is a quality metric that does not directly include appearance features in its judgment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-957813961c6bd225bcd390b432783050&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#quality_level_distribution&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="First Inspection Column">
      <data key="d0">First Inspection Column</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_FIRST_INSPECTION is a database column that stores the result of the first inspection for each coil.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Labeling Column">
      <data key="d0">Labeling Column</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_LABELING is a database column that indicates the final labeling or grade after labeling, distinct from the first inspection.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lab Report Configuration">
      <data key="d0">Lab Report Configuration</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">lab_report_config is a configuration table that stores settings, such as the level names for the first inspection pass rate calculation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Level Names Field">
      <data key="d0">Level Names Field</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_LEVEL_NAMES is a field in lab_report_config that configures which grades are considered passing for the first inspection pass rate (e.g., 'A').</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Single Coil Weight">
      <data key="d0">Single Coil Weight</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_SINGLE_COIL_WEIGHT is a database column that stores the weight of a single coil.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Delete Mark">
      <data key="d0">Delete Mark</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_DeleteMark is a database column used for soft deletion; records with F_DeleteMark IS NULL or 0 are included.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lab Intermediate Data">
      <data key="d0">Lab Intermediate Data</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">lab_intermediate_data is a database table from which the first inspection pass rate is calculated.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pass Weight">
      <data key="d0">Pass Weight</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">pass_weight is a calculated sum of F_SINGLE_COIL_WEIGHT for coils where F_FIRST_INSPECTION is in the configured passing levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Weight">
      <data key="d0">Total Weight</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">total_weight is the sum of all F_SINGLE_COIL_WEIGHT for non-deleted records.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pass Rate">
      <data key="d0">Pass Rate</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">pass_rate is the calculated percentage of pass_weight divided by total_weight.&lt;SEP&gt;A metric representing the proportion of qualified items, referenced in typical user questions as "合格率".</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ffe127439929c413f3cda62f238993b</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#daily_trend</data>
      <data key="d5">1778986084</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="A Grade Coil Weight">
      <data key="d0">A Grade Coil Weight</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A Grade Coil Weight is the total weight of coils labeled as 'A' based on F_LABELING, which is a common misconception for the first inspection pass rate.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Quality Grade Distribution">
      <data key="d0">Quality Grade Distribution</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Quality Grade Distribution is the proportion of coils in each final grade based on F_LABELING, distinct from the first inspection pass rate.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Grade Distribution is a metric calculated from F_LABELING data, showing the breakdown of final grades among items.&lt;SEP&gt;A metric that describes the distribution of labeling grades by weight, calculated by grouping by F_LABELING and summing coil weights, with nulls displayed as "Unlabeled", and sorted by weight descending.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-957813961c6bd225bcd390b432783050</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#quality_level_distribution</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985337</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F_PROD_DATE">
      <data key="d0">F_PROD_DATE</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_PROD_DATE is a database column within the `lab_intermediate_data` table that stores production dates. It serves as a core field in the Time dimension and is used extensively in SQL queries for filtering records within a specified date range, typically appearing in the WHERE clause of SQL templates. The column is also employed for grouping data in queries. Synonyms for F_PROD_DATE include the Chinese terms 生产日期, 生产日, and 日期, as well as the alias `prod_date`. As a date column, it enables efficient retrieval and analysis of data based on production timelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Column in lab_intermediate_data representing the production date.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-957813961c6bd225bcd390b432783050&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e6e25c9fd58e9924568e84459192dcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e53f732c8785683f40dd43eb1120bf26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a89346ef582d2491429fb4a619ba0c4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaa469fa109e3da0e7694dbe4aa14741&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-985990948d7ec4a2a0aaa3d3376e6d0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1ffe127439929c413f3cda62f238993b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8158b31ac0e5f48421ac68e0c0b5873</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#quality_level_distribution&lt;SEP&gt;aliases.json#field&lt;SEP&gt;dimensions_meta.json#time&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#metric_aggregate&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#metric_rate&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#shift_comparison&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#daily_trend&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#unqualified_breakdown</data>
      <data key="d5">1778986125</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="SQL Query">
      <data key="d0">SQL Query</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The SQL Query is a code snippet that calculates the First Inspection Pass Rate by summing coil weights and filtering based on first inspection results.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Common Misunderstanding">
      <data key="d0">Common Misunderstanding</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Common Misunderstanding refers to the mistaken belief that the ratio of A-grade coil weight to total weight (based on F_LABELING) equals the First Inspection Pass Rate (based on F_FIRST_INSPECTION).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f2504a9381d2837c8dd322280d321c43</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#first_inspection_rate</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985158</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F_FIRST_INSPECTION">
      <data key="d0">F_FIRST_INSPECTION</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_FIRST_INSPECTION is a database column representing the first inspection result (e.g., A, performance nonconformity, extreme difference nonconformity). It is unchangeable and reflects the production process quality; used for calculating the first inspection pass rate and failure reason analysis.&lt;SEP&gt;A database column for first inspection results, mentioned as not used in the Quality Grade Distribution calculation.&lt;SEP&gt;Column in lab_intermediate_data representing the first inspection category.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-957813961c6bd225bcd390b432783050&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8158b31ac0e5f48421ac68e0c0b5873</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#quality_level_distribution&lt;SEP&gt;sql_templates.json#unqualified_breakdown</data>
      <data key="d5">1778986125</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F_LABELING">
      <data key="d0">F_LABELING</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_LABELING is a database column representing the final labeling grade after rework or reinspection (e.g., A, B, not labeled). It may be upgraded due to rework; used for calculating quality grade distribution and shipment grade statistics.&lt;SEP&gt;A database column used for grouping in the Quality Grade Distribution calculation; represents the labeling grade.&lt;SEP&gt;Database field representing final grade and labeling, with synonyms: 最终等级, 总判定, 贴标.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-957813961c6bd225bcd390b432783050&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e6e25c9fd58e9924568e84459192dcc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge_base.json#quality_level_distribution&lt;SEP&gt;aliases.json#field</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985698</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rework">
      <data key="d0">Rework</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Rework is the process of repairing defective items, which can upgrade the F_LABELING grade.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reinspection">
      <data key="d0">Reinspection</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reinspection is the process of re-inspecting items after rework, affecting the final F_LABELING grade.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Production Process">
      <data key="d0">Production Process</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Production Process is the manufacturing phase where the first inspection occurs; its quality is reflected by the unchangeable F_FIRST_INSPECTION column.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Final Shipment Grade">
      <data key="d0">Final Shipment Grade</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Final Shipment Grade is the grade assigned to items for shipment, determined by F_LABELING after possible rework and reinspection.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985217</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nonconformity Reason Analysis">
      <data key="d0">Nonconformity Reason Analysis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Nonconformity Reason Analysis is an analysis use case for F_FIRST_INSPECTION data to investigate the causes of nonconforming products.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1d48176026da03bdf3116a649b995b85</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#labeling_vs_first_inspection</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985217</data>
