      <data key="d5">1778985373</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Batch Number">
      <data key="d0">Batch Number</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Batch Number is a uniform identifier for multiple coils within the same furnace, stored in the field F_FURNACE_BATCH_NO. It is also known as批次号, 炉次号, or Furnace Batch Number.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-60d113a19c7939fa4f4a548b3cc1eba5</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_batch_no</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985408</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F_FURNACE_BATCH_NO">
      <data key="d0">F_FURNACE_BATCH_NO</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">F_FURNACE_BATCH_NO is a database field that stores the batch number for a group of coils within the same furnace.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-60d113a19c7939fa4f4a548b3cc1eba5</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_batch_no</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985408</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coil">
      <data key="d0">Coil</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Coil is a physical unit of steel product. Multiple coils can be within the same furnace run, and each coil has a unique furnace number.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-60d113a19c7939fa4f4a548b3cc1eba5</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_batch_no</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985408</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Furnace Run">
      <data key="d0">Furnace Run</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Furnace Run is a production batch of steel from the same furnace, identified by a batch number, and can contain multiple coils.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-60d113a19c7939fa4f4a548b3cc1eba5</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#furnace_batch_no</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985408</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Appearance Feature">
      <data key="d0">Appearance Feature</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Appearance Feature refers to surface characteristics or defects of strip material identified by naked eye or instruments, typically written in Chinese characters at the end of furnace numbers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brittle">
      <data key="d0">Brittle</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brittle is an appearance feature meaning easily broken or cracked, with synonyms like brittle-prone.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Scratch">
      <data key="d0">Scratch</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Scratch is an appearance feature meaning surface scratch or mark, with synonyms like scratch mark.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pitting">
      <data key="d0">Pitting</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pitting is an appearance feature meaning pockmarked surface defect, with synonyms like pitted surface.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dent">
      <data key="d0">Dent</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dent is an appearance feature meaning surface depression, with synonyms like sunken area.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ridge">
      <data key="d0">Ridge</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ridge is an appearance feature meaning unevenness or sharp edge, with synonyms like raised edge.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="White Edge">
      <data key="d0">White Edge</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">White Edge is an appearance feature meaning whitening at the edge of the strip.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brittle Edge">
      <data key="d0">Brittle Edge</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brittle Edge is an appearance feature meaning the edge is easily broken or fragile.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
      <data key="d5">1778985452</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bright Line">
      <data key="d0">Bright Line</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Bright Line is an appearance feature meaning a bright streak on the surface.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-03f8b5b2f4b11326c72d680e9f3f0c64</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge_base.json#appearance_features</data>
