    <node id="LLM">
      <data key="d0">LLM</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A language model referenced for generating SQL queries based on the provided template.&lt;SEP&gt;LLM stands for Large Language Model, which is referenced as the target for generating SQL queries based on the SQL skeleton.&lt;SEP&gt;LLM (Large Language Model) is used to generate SQL queries with an understanding of business semantics provided by the semantic layer.&lt;SEP&gt;LLM (Large Language Model) is used in the SQL correction loop to generate corrected SQL based on original SQL, error message, and DDL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a89346ef582d2491429fb4a619ba0c4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaa469fa109e3da0e7694dbe4aa14741&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e7b2af007d32a6e2000a0941bbd36f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e376f7f6a81dd4706f50d07a152fe75d</data>
