    <node id="CUSTOM">
      <data key="d0">CUSTOM</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CUSTOM is a source type indicator used in data systems, signifying that a column, variable, or formula is defined by a custom definition rather than a predefined or standard source. It serves as a keyword that indicates the source type of a column is custom-defined, often applied to calculations, formulas, or variables that are not derived from built-in or default sources. In practice, CUSTOM denotes that the column's source type is based on a custom formula, a custom-defined calculation—for example, one used for computing a front average (前部平均值)—or any other custom specification. It is a consistent label across various contexts, appearing as a source type for columns, variables, and formulas, all of which share the core meaning of being user-defined or non-standard. The descriptions collectively affirm that CUSTOM is a uniform term representing a custom source type, with no conflicting interpretations or multiple distinct entities.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0d38c813d65d921fdc47047da8bea580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5e71c3c828b1794cd7ab677f8e4186b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-032a1a4ee358fe216b673a5d8fdf4694&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ac45d7fbc81903cad80d3a7a95f7065&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-793dc28add8634f1fe7cf84b5a846318&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b9dd172ddf40c0bdd07bbae68d11796&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a5fff8a9a17a09937473ac956f254b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24c82aa0157addf5eedfe661109c1996</data>
      <data key="d4">Neo4j:Formula:787025213026992069&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787025434377191365&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787030712749391813&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031085417496517&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031280893034437&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031424921239493&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031496698363845&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031710205214661</data>
      <data key="d5">1779045693</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="μm">
      <data key="d0">μm</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">μm (micrometer) is a unit of measurement equal to one millionth of a meter (10⁻⁶ m). It is used to quantify small distances, thicknesses, and differences in scale, and is commonly applied to indicate the precision or magnitude of values in various contexts, such as computed averages, variable outputs, or column-level measurements. As a metric unit, μm provides a standardized way to express fine dimensions in scientific, engineering, and industrial settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0d38c813d65d921fdc47047da8bea580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5e71c3c828b1794cd7ab677f8e4186b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-032a1a4ee358fe216b673a5d8fdf4694&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ac45d7fbc81903cad80d3a7a95f7065&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-793dc28add8634f1fe7cf84b5a846318&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b9dd172ddf40c0bdd07bbae68d11796&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a5fff8a9a17a09937473ac956f254b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24c82aa0157addf5eedfe661109c1996</data>
      <data key="d4">Neo4j:Formula:787025213026992069&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787025434377191365&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787030712749391813&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031085417496517&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031280893034437&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031424921239493&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031496698363845&lt;SEP&gt;Neo4j:Formula:787031710205214661</data>
      <data key="d5">1779045693</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
