    <node id="Detection">
      <data key="d0">Detection</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Detection is a data field or range used in the formula MIN(RANGE(Detection, 1, 5)).&lt;SEP&gt;Detection is a dataset or array from which values are extracted for computing the Front Maximum.&lt;SEP&gt;Detection is a set of measurements or data points used as input to the average calculation over a range of indices 1 to 5.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-032a1a4ee358fe216b673a5d8fdf4694&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bb2feeb0b6ec752ec572f96dc466ee7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ac45d7fbc81903cad80d3a7a95f7065</data>
